INSERT INTO issue VALUES(883,'883','2015-04-14T08:39:57Z',468,9,'HGustavs','Closed','It is possible to have different marks in dugga and in corresponding kursmoment','Right now the dugga system suffers from a disparity in how marks are handled between duga and in delkurs. It is now possible to have UG in a dugga and UGVG in the corresponding moment. The user interface needs to be connected better in some way. Dugga-entries are rarely changed and need to be safeguarded against accidental deletions  since it must be REALLY REALLY IMPOSSIBLE to  accidentally or on purpose  delete the results of a student after-the-fact . I liked parts of the suggestion of moving the dugga into the course editor... but did not like what it did to the user interface. My suggestion is to go in the opposite direction  to have more access the course information in the dugga view. This way the course interface is still un-cluttered  but the more rarely used dugga interface  allows us to both manage the dugga and connect it to the course elements. This way the marking can be kept consistent.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(885,'885','2015-04-14T08:50:33Z',468,9,'HGustavs','Closed','New course version dialog - copy from version','I believe that there is no working dialog for creating a new version of a course. This is a pretty complicated task as it is necessary to copy some contents from the old version to the new version including but not limited to the course layout and any references in that course layout to things such as code examples  which also need to be duplicated . I think this is a superficially simple issue but I do believe that it is an infinitely deep rabbit-hole.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1072,'1072','2015-04-25T16:03:35Z',479,17,'HGustavs','Closed','Remove code standard.js','Right now we have two code standards  one .js and one .md. I vote for keeping only the md one so we dont end up with two conflicting code standards.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1073,'1073','2015-04-25T16:14:59Z',479,17,'HGustavs','Closed','Demo course','I suggest adding some information from a real course to test the dugga and code viewer systems. The most advanced and varied course that uses the old version is shaderprogrammering. If the shaderprogrammering course can be entered into the system and if navigation works for that course we are very close a working system. Shaderprogrammering 2015 We cannot be sure that everything works as intended if we do not add real data as example content. The testing data in the databasecode examples right now is too limited to test if the course content works as we want it to.');
