INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1816,'1816','2015-11-01T19:37:26Z',669,20,'HGustavs','Closed','A left view split template in code viewer','We lack a template for situations when there are two views on the left e.g. a short description and a preview in the left half of the screen and a longer piece of code on the right. So in short  a mirror flip of the one large two smaller template.... making it a two smaller one large split instead.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1817,'1817','2015-11-01T19:41:15Z',669,20,'HGustavs','Closed','coloring of html in code viewer','Right now HTML or XML is colored black in the code viewer. A much better way would to give it a separate color e.g. green.... so it is easier to identify html code mixed with javascript or php.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1818,'1818','2015-11-01T19:52:12Z',669,20,'HGustavs','Closed','The important word highlighting does not work with strings','If for instance I want to highlight a specific identifier e.g. input1 it does not work neither if one writes input1 or if one writes input1. Either andor both should work. It would be of great benefit to be able to show how a certain piece of javascript relates to corresponding html using the identifier.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1819,'1819','2015-11-01T21:19:09Z',669,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Setting Up New Code Example','Right now  too many clicks  and other interactions  are required for setting up a new code example. Presumably  one example is similar to the next  when we click new example  a copy of the layout of the previous exmple should be created. Right now it is empty. This requires lots of clicks to set up a code example  and most code examples require the same sequence of actions. Section name and Example title need to be copied from the section editor so that we enter those names in one single place. However if we want to change that default we can if we want to. The kinds of content can also be copied if the previous example uses 1  2 3 split then the next one will probably use that also. If it uses code for 1  preview for 2 and description for 3 the next exmple will probably also use this layout.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1820,'1820','2015-11-02T08:20:13Z',670,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Play controls for gif animations','It would be a great addition if we could add play controls to the gif animations in showdoc. https:github.combuzzfeedlibgif-js');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1821,'1821','2015-11-02T09:33:20Z',670,10,'HGustavs','Closed','Important word feature request','Important word currently has problems with over-finding important words. If the important word is click the parser also finds the first part of the word clicked. I suggest searching for space click space  or something of that nature  in the document view.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1822,'1822','2015-11-02T09:48:07Z',670,10,'HGustavs','Closed','List filters in code viewer','The lists could be filtered more agressively. I feel that removing .md from the list of code files would be acceptable. If one wants to show markdown in the code viewer one could easily change the extension to .md in those cases.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1823,'1823','2015-11-02T10:49:23Z',670,11,'HGustavs','Closed','More icons in section editor','The section editor would benefit from having icons for the functions such as files  tests access and so on moved into the top menu  like in the code viewer. The reason for this is that when we have many files in a course the menu moves out of sight. I suggest making icons like in the code viewer.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1824,'1824','2015-11-02T10:56:19Z',670,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Code viewer css support','It would be interesting to see if we could push the envelope a bit when it comes to css support in the code viewer. Much like we did for html support. Imagine hovering over a css declaration .someclass if the corresponding divs e.g. would highlight that would increase the readability of css declaration for novice htmlcss-ists.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1825,'1825','2015-11-09T11:25:00Z',677,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Updated since last visit.','It would appreciate some kind of stop light or other symbol to denote that some items have been updated since my last visit. This includes courses  code examples and other things. It should not be possible to confuse the last update with the assignment stoplights. other than that any notation that works is fine.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1826,'1826','2015-11-09T15:50:31Z',677,16,'HGustavs','Closed','Faux-Deletion of Dugga Variant','Deletion of duggavariant may not happen if one has been used in an answer. The best way to handle this is to NEVER delete anything. But what if a dugga-variant is erroneous and it HAS to be deleted. I suggest  is there a better approach?  a disabled button to keep a variant  and therefore keep any links to previous answers  but disallow it from being used in future dugga-s.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1827,'1827','2015-11-24T10:27:48Z',692,11,'a97marbr','Closed','Informative title  e.g.  filename  instead of showdoc.php','I would like the page title to reflect which file that has been opened instead of saying showdoc.php.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1828,'1828','2015-11-29T18:12:31Z',697,19,'HGustavs','Closed','Important word bug','If one uses the same important word twice the code breaks in a funny way... and javascript is pasted in clear text in the description window. Make sure that is is not possible to add an important word that has been added before.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1829,'1829','2015-11-29T18:50:36Z',697,19,'HGustavs','Closed','Button to retrieve section name and example name','I think that one simple way to solve the bugs that do with section and example name for the code examples would be a button to automatically copying current section and current example name from the section table. The other previous way that was suggested in another issue is to make this process completely automatic. Perhaps a one-button solution could work as well?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1830,'1830','2015-11-29T19:48:48Z',697,20,'HGustavs','Closed','Third visibility','In the section editor  there was previously a requirement to have login required in addition to public and hidden. This means that a code example or other document only will be shown if the user is logged in. I believe this previously was a requirement?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1831,'1831','2015-11-29T20:12:18Z',697,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Markdown suggestion','We have a file in the repository called markdownsuggestion.md this is better handled by the issue system. It would be nice to have a markdown tag for the hr tag  if there is no standardized way I suggest four dashes: ---- or four equals ==== for the hr tag.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1832,'1832','2015-11-29T20:23:00Z',697,21,'HGustavs','Closed','File updated log','We have made issues for creating logs for page views and file downloads etc I would also like to have a log of all file uploads to be able to graph the update rate of a file.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1833,'1833','2015-11-29T22:40:12Z',697,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Important words','I am not sure if this issue has been reported before.... but... if I have an important word in the code viewer... for example Train the important word-code will mark the first half of Trainset also. This is not correct behavior. It should be possible to have both train and trainset as important words independently. I suggest using regular expressions when searching for important words in the descriptions... and add support for white space  parenthesis or other dividers but if there is none  there should be no match.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1834,'1834','2015-11-29T23:25:06Z',698,0,'HGustavs','Closed','Tabs need to be converted to spaces in code viewer','One major problem with the code viewer is the size of the tabs. They are HUGE. I am thinking along the lines of replacing all tabs with 2 or 4 spaces. I think we implemented this feature a long time ago but it does not seem to work... perhaps that code was removed for some reason?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1835,'1835','2015-12-03T18:43:38Z',701,19,'HGustavs','Closed','File upload functionality','The file uploading view needs some additional features: Size of file and upload date Link to Preview of file by clicking on the name of the file');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1836,'1836','2015-12-06T10:35:29Z',704,11,'HGustavs','Closed','New Template','I sorely miss a code viewer template that has two boxes to the left and one to the right. e.g. Description and preview on the left and code on the right. This allows a taller code window while still retaining the preview. e.g. this is a left-to right flip of the 3rd template');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1837,'1837','2015-12-06T10:52:11Z',704,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Section editor interactivity','It would be nice to have a helpful button for sections. For example a hide-all button for sections that hide all elements inside  below  that section. there may be other buttons with similar functionality that may be useful ');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1838,'1838','2015-12-06T20:19:22Z',704,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Bug in preview window in code viewer','It seems like the preview window only works if placed at the bottom right. I tried to use template 3 three views  left pane  top and bottom right. Preview works to the right but not to the left.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1839,'1839','2015-12-07T12:10:47Z',705,13,'HGustavs','Closed','Some tables lack logging features','In addition to the normal user logging  which hardly works anyhow  We lack latest update columns on some tables e.g. the Vers table lacks this  we cannot see when the version was last createdupdated.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1840,'1840','2015-12-10T12:21:41Z',708,13,'HGustavs','Closed','Mailto email when lenasys course has been changed.','semi-automatically e-mailing the students through an mailto email link using the normal email client but with automatically generated message would be an awesome addition.');
