INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1957,'1957','2016-04-01T21:24:48Z',821,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Stability logging','As we are having  rare - at most weekly  crashes due to unknown reasons logging for stability reasons is needed quite fast. This is along the lines of what we need Generate a random ID in client application before calling service and pass this with the call to the service along with client timestamp Pass random ID and timestamp to service service logs when form data is received Save ID  client time and server local timestamp to log Execute Service At end of service  just before or after json encode  get current server timestamp and save it to log When data is received in client send local client timestamp to server. If we now read the log we have the following information Client start timestamp Server start timestamp Server end timestamp Client end timestamp With this we can trace any request and see how much time it takes and if the last two steps are missing or very long  we know that a crash has ocurred or that performance is bad. We can even trace the exact data to the anomaly. First three steps do not add additional requests to the network  only the id and timestamp  which are minute in comparison to rest of data  A configuration switch to disable the fourth round-trip step would be needed as it adds a network request that was not present previously  in a constrained network  having the ability to disable this un-necessary network request would be a good thing.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1958,'1958','2016-04-01T21:27:26Z',821,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Logging database','The logging needs to work with an external database. Currently the logging uses the same database as the rest of the information. This is sub-optimal  since it clogs up the main database with logs. And also  logging can use a lighter interface since we are only appending information  never deleting  and rarely selecting information from the log. I suggest moving all of the logging operations to an sqlite database or even using a specialized logging layer with options for log storage such as mysql  postgres  sqlite or a text file depending on performance needs.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1959,'1959','2016-04-01T21:29:51Z',821,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Log preview window','Also  some kind of network issue window for the admnistrator with graphs that show this data would be nice.... Examples of thing we would like to see in this view: which service is the slowest? which service is used the most? are there any crashes or slowdowns and if so  in what service? are we being attacked by for instance password guessing applications? Graphs using html5 canvas.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1960,'1960','2016-04-01T21:51:55Z',821,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Markdown image zoom rollover','I would like to have some kind of support for something like the images in this page in the markdown http:wwwlab.iit.his.segushShaderprogrammeringOldAssignment3.html When we rollover the image it is shown in its original size but normally it is only a thumbnail. This way it is easier to follow the layout of the page  without it being cluttered with large images.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(1961,'1961','2016-04-02T08:15:17Z',822,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Get rid of external css file for hack and place in main css','One thing that makes things hard to find is using different css files for different things. We want things in one place  one css file  one declaration for each kind of thing to make things as easy as possible to find. We are using an external css  hack-extended.min.css  file in the code viewer for the hack font... this needs to be moved to the main file');
