INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2065,'2065','2016-04-08T08:50:38Z',828,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Forum does not fit with system architecture','So.... Reviewing the code of the forum module  there are some changes that need to be made. The layout for all code in the project is as follows: blabla.php  any static content  blablaService.php  receives the database updates  and sends data in json to application  blabla.js  Sends data to service and renders result in json using javascript  so by that standard the code should contain only the files listed below No html in the php files and all database access in Service file. I am fine with putting the forum in a folder  but it could also be placed in the duggasys folder. forum.php forumService.php forum.js');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2066,'2066','2016-04-08T08:56:39Z',828,9,'HGustavs','Closed','code viewer does not comply with general layout.','For legacy reasons the code viewer component does not fit 100% with the general architecture of the system. The files are currently called EditorV50.php codeviewer.js editorService.php How large would the implications be of fixing this? In the ideal case we could just change the names to: codeviewer.php codeviewer.js codeviewerService.php ...and move the files to the duggaSys folder. and nothing bad would happen. However... I think that we need to change a few more places  for instance there is a link in the duggasys section editor that needs to be changed so that the link points to codeviewer.php instead of ..codviewerEditorv50.php ... A few links to shared files or folders need to be re-jigged to fit... Is this fix so small that it can be made without completely crashing the system??');
