INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2186,'2186','2016-04-19T10:36:45Z',839,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Save button fix.','Along with the code that gray-es out the save button in a dugga if the user is not logged in  it would also be nice to gray the button out if nothing has changed. Example: A user writes something in a text-submit window or A user presses browse button to select one or more files ... If the person then presses save without pressing upload first  nothing happens. This is clearly a problem as students have reported submitting content to a course  but the only thing visible to teachers is an empty view. so... Solution  save is grayed out until upload has been pressed in some part of the generic dugga view. If there is more than one upload button  one is sufficient  it is not necessary to both upload a zip file and a document to press save  it should be possible to add new files later and press save again. Im not sure if this is specific only for generic_file_upload or for all duga-save-button-presses.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2219,'2219','2016-04-22T06:25:02Z',842,7,'a97marbr','Closed','Submissions of duggas causes problems when non-ascii characters are used','When submitting files through the dugga system  i.e.  using the generic-file-receive-dugga we get a problem with malformed file paths if we have Swedish characters in the filename or file path. min_fil.zip works min_l├Ñda.zip does not work');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2277,'2277','2016-04-28T11:48:52Z',848,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Faster Workflow in Code Viewer','I would like a way to assign files to all views at once. Right now it is Select Template  Ok  Cog Wheel First View  Select File  Ok  Cog Wheel Second View  Select File  Ok  Cog Wheel Third View  Select File  Ok  Cog Wheel Fourth View  Select File  Ok ... I would like a workflow that works like this: Select Template  Below the template selection images  in same view there are file dropdowns for View1  View2 View3 View4 for selecting Kind  Language  if appropriate  and File for each. This way  most of the work CAN be done in the template selection window  and it can then be changed by the current normal way of doing it with the cog wheels.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2283,'2283','2016-04-28T14:53:29Z',848,15,'andras-marki','Open','Possible systematic testing after weekly merge','At the moment  the group leaders have the responsibility to check that everything works nicely after the weekly merge. The problem here is  that everything works nicely is quite ill-defined. We have no maintained requirement list  so testing against it is pretty much infeasible. We could use some form of coverage criteria  but that would result in a lot of extra work. I think the bare minimum should be some list on the already implemented features  plus features added under the week. The list should act as a ground for  a maintained list  of test cases  where each test is coupled to a given feature  with a description on the required system state  for example a user should be logged in   with the activity  ex. Webbutveckling is opened on the course list  and an expected outcome  The content of Webbutveckling is displayed . The problem here would be that we have one  or two  lists which should be maintained too. The gain is that we have an actual list on what and how is checked after a merge  so we know at least what we test and what do we have for quality on those parts we test. This could in my view result in that we wouldnt have similar problems as we did on last Friday. This could also help the issue with seeing failures  bugs propagating visible to the user  on the webpage when the person testing the system forgot to update for example the DBS rights. Any thoughts about this?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2300,'2300','2016-05-02T09:39:24Z',852,10,'HGustavs','Closed','Code viewer mobile adaptation','There used to be css that makes strange things with the code viewer if the window is thin or very narrow. ... What I would prefer is a hotdog-menu hamburger menu  it seems like food-related metaphors are common for that kind of button . That would show only one of the parts of the screen. And I would like this to be handled through the get-link  so if one presses the first menu item we would navigate to the same page again  but with &showpane=1 added to the url. Mockup: On mobile that view could conceivably be the default view. Perhaps at the button of the dropdown  a show deskop buttonicon could be an additional alternative. This should theoretically be a fairly simple change as we would not need to mess much with the templatemultiple view system  and no adaptive css is necessary. And one could navigate to an expanded view or bookmark one through the get-link. The three alternatives in the menu should thus link back to the code viewer but with &showpane=1 &showpane=2 &showpane=3 This should make the code viewer very useful even on mobile. [https:cloud.githubusercontent.comassets697880114951519d4df76ba-1059-11e6-9cba-adf8372d031e.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2304,'2304','2016-05-02T10:54:19Z',852,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Crashes in code viewer','In some views the code viewer crashes when you click the cog wheel The culprit seems to be these lines: box[5]=box[5].replace &#47;g   ; $ #filename .val box[5] ; In some cases there is no box[5] in the data returned from the service. A check to make sure that box[5] exists and only execute the code if it does  and to perform some other alternative code if it does not  will hopefully resolve this issue?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2414,'2414','2016-08-17T15:11:12Z',959,16,'a97marbr','Closed','List entry with will void the ability to change the entry name','If we write a list entry such as Egons lecture this will render the row impossible to change.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2415,'2415','2016-10-31T10:16:16Z',1034,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Set as default option in Copy Course Version Does Nothing','Pretty much what title says... you have to click edit version in section editor to set as default.....');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2416,'2416','2016-10-31T10:19:02Z',1034,11,'HGustavs','Open','Course code dropdown list','Currently the course  version  code is a text box  we would prefer if you could paste this information into a list for all courses  making this a choise from a dropdown list. However in the interest of generality we want this to be a on select-copy-to-textbox function  so that you could have two versions of same course for example 20146a 20146b ... Paste-box for course names and codes would be nice if it is in same dialog. also  separate table in database.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2417,'2417','2016-10-31T11:14:49Z',1034,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Login timeout','The login timeout is probably the most grievence-causing issue so far. A student may be working for a long time on an exam or a teacher may likewise be working on reading a document for a long time  if the system times out during this time  no change is visible on screen. Make the timeout visible on screen  either by polling every minute30 seconds etc  or some other means When one logs back in  the redirect should return to the same page  not to the main page. Currently one has to click the login button twice  once to log out once to log in again. Even though the user already has been logged out through the timeout.....');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2418,'2418','2016-10-31T11:32:16Z',1034,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Delete variant in dugga editor does not refresh page properly','After refresh it looks fine. Unclear if it is an error of some kind or only lack of refresh.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2419,'2419','2016-10-31T11:43:52Z',1034,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Logging does not happen for you do not have permission to view this page','One worthwhile effort would be to give us more information on what pages people have tried to view outside the normal pages. Is it possible to replace the standard apache error page with a php-variant which uses logging  and also a redirect to the correct home page?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2420,'2420','2016-11-02T20:41:48Z',1036,21,'a97marbr','Closed','We need some kind of past deadline notice','When a student is submitting a dugga that has a deadline that is passed there should be some kind of configurable message. Some courses would say Deadline has passed. No more grading will be done until next time the course is given Another course could have a different approach: Deadline has passed. Grading will be done if the teachers have time. Otherwise next time the course is given I propose some kind of icon  a warning sign symbol?  together with the yellow stop light to indicate that this dugga is not guaranteed to be marked.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2421,'2421','2016-11-02T20:43:11Z',1036,21,'a97marbr','Closed','Codeviewer is not reading course local files','As title says. Having a course file  global to specific course e.g. Database Systems  file1.md And uploading a course local file  local to course version e.g. Database Systems VT17  file1.md The latter should be loaded. This does not happen at the moment.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2422,'2422','2016-11-23T11:14:12Z',1057,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Course page design through import','I would really like the posibility of creating a course page by importing markdown -# Course Goal 1  7.5HP  -* Code Example 1 ==ex1.js== -* Code Example 2 ==ex2.js== -* Test 1 ==test1.md== -# Course Goal 2  7.5HP  -* Code Example 3 ==ex3.js== -* Code Example 4 ==ex4.js== -* Test 2 ==test2.md== This way it would be possible to generate a course page skeleton very fast  rather than by clicking and writing things many times.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2423,'2423','2016-12-12T13:28:41Z',1076,14,'a97marbr','Closed','Result editor: Magic heading is not using correct width','If the size of the columns are larger than the minimum allowed the magic headings are not of proper size.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2424,'2424','2016-12-12T13:31:04Z',1076,14,'a97marbr','Closed','Result editor: The active sorted column is not displayed properly','We do not have the right coloring on the magic heading for the column being sorted on.');
