INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2450,'2450','2017-02-21T08:09:17Z',1147,9,'a97marbr','Open','Enable view of statistics about number of times a dugga has been marked','It would be nice to be able to tell how many times a dugga has been marked. This would be useful to Tell if a dugga is hardunclear - the amount of duggas that require more than 2 markings is too hardunclear Rank duggas in terms of how hard they are We could perhaps implement something that ask a student to see tutor if dugga has been marked as fail more than 2 times');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2451,'2451','2017-02-21T13:41:12Z',1147,14,'a97marbr','Closed','An overview regarding duggas and how they are allocated during a course','I would like to have some kind of service that shows the outline of how the various duggas should be connected. For example  which duggas are required to be done before others  which duggas canshould be done in parallel? For this to work we need to know when a dugga is intended to start as well as when it should finish. A moment  delkurs  should be a swim lane We need a suggested starting time for a dugga We need deadlines for duggas The required amount of time needed to finish a task should be visible in the length of the lines. For example the blue task requires less time than the pink task Perhaps we should have some indication on when students are supposed to receive feedback on duggas? [https:cloud.githubusercontent.comassets4948661231667954447624e-f842-11e6-966a-31e6e0e95eef.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2452,'2452','2017-02-23T08:35:39Z',1149,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Teachers are present in marking view','In the marking view  if a teacher has been added to the course  that person will be in the list of students for marking. It is good to have oneself to test marking with  but there should be an option to remove teachers from the list... especially for counting students this is very useful... with the current system it is easy to accidentally cont teachers.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2453,'2453','2017-02-28T10:19:45Z',1154,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Examiner is not present visible in result marking view','In final year projects  the examiner is not visible in the marking list. We need to add the following. In access view for a course we add an examiner dropdown which allows the course responsible to rapidly specify the examiner for each student. We need to show the name of the examiner in the list in the marking view.  sorting on examiner is an added benefit ');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2454,'2454','2017-02-28T10:30:56Z',1154,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram Engine Functionality','The diagram engine should work mostly like the engine from google docs Each instance of a diagram has a unique hash Each instance is represented as a json text document Not every minor change triggers an instance  moving an element or resizing it should not trigger changes  The engine allows one user of a diagram to query the engine if a diagram has been updated by sending diagram id and receiving the latest hash If the hash is not identical with the local hash  the complete document string is retrieved If a single user is editing and no other users are viewing the document we only do writing to the diagram.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2455,'2455','2017-02-28T10:48:13Z',1154,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Offline diagramming','Since the diagramming engine works through reading or writing json documents  an offline or slow-internet version of the engine should be possible e.g. by storing the diagram in local storage and ony infrequently updating the on-server document.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2456,'2456','2017-02-28T11:17:31Z',1154,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagramming engine refresh rates','Refresh of the diagrams should be timer-based. If last edit of diagram was recent  update time should be short also  down to a few seconds. If last edit of diagram was not recent  hours to days  minute-based updates should be used If diagram has not been edited for several days  a week +   diagram should essentially be read-once only  and update status should only be queried on refresh.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2457,'2457','2017-02-28T11:24:00Z',1154,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagramming engine should have native to-svg-support','Each drawing operation in a diagram should have the option to draw to a svg string instead of only to the screen. Much like the mostly dormant DiagrammingSYS project. https:github.comHGustavsDiagrammingSYS This way we can export the diagram to svg without much effort.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2458,'2458','2017-02-28T11:25:59Z',1154,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagramming system should be based on the box model duga code','LenaSYSDuggaSystemplatesboxmodell.js');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2459,'2459','2017-03-01T11:54:18Z',1155,12,'HGustavs','Closed','alternative colors for registered students in course view','I would like an ~~~alternating~~~ alternative color for any course that the student has been registered to in the course editor.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2460,'2460','2017-03-01T12:04:17Z',1155,13,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagramming Touch Handlers','In curve-dugga.js there is an attempt at handling touch drawing. It would be useful to add a similar approach to touch to the diagramming system. We would want to just convert touch to mouse events  no specific handling for touch that is different from normal mouse events  this way minimum changes are needed to any code.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2461,'2461','2017-03-18T17:32:38Z',1172,18,'a97marbr','Closed','Magic Headings Marking View - Columns','I would like to have magic headings on the columns in the resulted service. If a course have many duggas and we need to scroll horisontally  I would like to still see the rownumber and the student name in the same way as we see the dugga names when we scroll vertically.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2462,'2462','2017-03-18T17:38:38Z',1172,18,'a97marbr','Open','Dugga template - Seminar dugga','I would like to have a dugga template s  that provide a good way to represent registering to a seminar provide an automatic  or at least a semi-automatic  presentation scheme with optional number of opponents I believe that inspiration can be found in the feedback dugga and that we should divide this into a register for seminar dugga and a presentation scheme dugga');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2463,'2463','2017-03-18T17:44:54Z',1172,18,'a97marbr','Closed','Group assignment dugga template','I would like a group assignment dugga template. The major features of this is that we should have the ability to assign groups from the course rooster marking one submission in the group should automatically grade all group members submissions');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2464,'2464','2017-03-18T17:49:14Z',1172,18,'a97marbr','Closed','Email response for duggas','I would like to be able to contact students based on their results. For example: Inform all students who have not been active at all Inform students that a deadline is near Inform all students who have failed duggas More It is enough to have a feature that generates the list of recipients and a pre-generated subject and content. The actual sending of the email can be done by external email client.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2465,'2465','2017-03-18T17:52:51Z',1172,18,'a97marbr','Closed','Select all duggas all duggas in a moment','In the filtering option I would like to be able to quickly select allno duggas allno duggas from a particular moment');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2466,'2466','2017-03-21T18:28:10Z',1175,19,'HGustavs','Merged','Seeded diagramming and contribution modules','Automatically Merged Contribution and Diagramming Seeds');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2467,'2467','2017-03-22T22:30:43Z',1176,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Split diagram.js into parts','I think that diagram.js will be too big to fit the one function one file rule. I suggest we augment the code styleand specify that we allow additional class files if they are sizable  **1000 lines of code  and localized  used only in one module . I suggest using adding the class name to the name of the file e.g. diagram.js  for user interface stuff  diagram_diagram.js diagran_symbol.js diagram_figure.js etc. Indicating that it is part of the diagram module but that each sub-class  there will only be a few of these  has its own file. The goal is to keep as few of these files as possible.... but to separate diagram class from the symbol class.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2468,'2468','2017-03-27T11:44:41Z',1181,12,'HGustavs','Closed','Markdown smilies overtake other content','If one writes something that looks like a smilie such as for example SELECT * FROM PERSON WHERE SSN**MAX param:  ... the :  part is turned into a smilie we should look for white spacesmiliewhite space instead... this way we can write either smilies and also use parenthesis as intended originally.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2472,'2472','2017-03-29T06:58:36Z',1183,7,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram scaling','I suggest an implementation that uses view position  position of top left corner on screen  and a scale factor to draw graphics. Currently graphics are drawn without scaling a global scaling factor needs to be used in the draw method and when reading mouse and touch coordinates. It would be advantageous to have similar scaling for svg output  allowing us to fit more or less of the diagram on a svg image page.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2473,'2473','2017-03-29T07:00:58Z',1183,8,'HGustavs','Closed','Global settings for diagrams','A global settings dialog for the diagrams is needed in some way. Line thickness Default Colors Fonts of text in diagrams etc.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2483,'2483','2017-03-29T10:24:49Z',1183,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Merging of changes in strutt.sql into init_db.sql','In the file strutt.sql I found this content. I think that these changes also have to be added to the tables in the init_db if they have not already been added. alter table user_course alter column result SET DEFAULT 0.0; alter table user_course alter column period set default 1; alter table user_course alter column term set default 1; alter table user_course add column vershistory TEXT; alter table user_course add column vers VARCHAR 8 ; alter table codeexample MODIFY runlink VARCHAR 256 ;');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2576,'2576','2017-03-31T12:26:36Z',1185,13,'HGustavs','Closed','Interface for changing attribute type in diagram','We need an interface for changing attribute properties e.g. computed attribute  key attribute  compound attribute etc I suggest an attribute property dialog where we can modify both the name of the attribute and add an optional data type and also configure the kind of the attribute....');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2799,'2799','2017-04-06T06:54:47Z',1191,7,'a97marbr','Closed','Add a current course version column in the access service','When listing the users who has access to a course I would like a column that lists the course version that each user has as their active version. In the edit user dialog I would like to be able to change this. Preferably by selecting from a dropdown filled with available course versions.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2963,'2963','2017-04-11T07:32:52Z',1196,8,'HGustavs','Closed','Student view of group assignment','Im thinking that each seminar is a dugga  we have a setting for group or else for each section editor item  something like a dropdown  Normal  Group  Seminar  Group Seminar In the section editor if group or group seminar has been set we clearly show the assigned group number in the section editor heading. Mockup anyone?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2966,'2966','2017-04-11T07:54:33Z',1196,8,'HGustavs','Closed','Collapsability of sections on mobile','Collapsing sections is particularly useful on mobile  does the collapsing work as expected on mobile  and is the gesture for collapsing good enough or do we want to modify the behavior to better fit mobile use?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(2974,'2974','2017-04-11T08:24:39Z',1196,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Install script test data','We need more test data... for example A completely empty course More tests  duggas  More students assigned to courses More teachers assigned to courses  for testing teacher filtering ');
