INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4159,'4159','2017-08-09T09:53:51Z',1316,10,'a97marbr','Closed','File handling problem - How should we copy files between course versions?','The files used in a course uses a global -** course -** course version idea. This means that files uploaded as a global file is available to all courses. A file uploaded as a course file is available to all course versions of that course. A file uploaded to course local is only available to that specific course version. When retrieving a file we only specify a file name  and the system will serve the appropriate file using the preference rule local over course over global. When creating a new course version based on on an old course version we are faced with a problem. How should we chose files that have a local version? The overall goal is to have old course versions to be as they were and new course versions to have the most updated versions of files. Scenario 1: A file  file1.txt is created in HT15. The following year an updated version is created and put in course local files receiving a new id  id2 . The following year  HT17  we want this updated file to be used as the new regular course file and the field course local file should be empty. If we in HT17 change a typo in File1.txt this will be shown in HT17 and HT16 but not in HT15. == HT15 == -- Course Files -- id1  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- == HT16 == -- Course Files -- id1  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- id2  File1.txt == HT17 == -- Course Files -- id2  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- For this to work I think we need a path column in the fileLink table to be able to located the most current file. Scenario 2: A file  file1.txt is created in HT15. The following year we create a unique version of file1.txt and put in course local files receiving a new id  id2 . The following year  HT17  we dont want the unique file created previous year but rather the course file created HT15. Course local files should be empty. If we in HT17 change a typo in File1.txt this will be shown in HT17 and HT15 but not in HT16. == HT15 == -- Course Files -- id1  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- == HT16 == -- Course Files -- id1  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- id2  File1.txt == HT17 == -- Course Files -- id1  File1.txt -- Course Local Files -- This does not require a new column in fileLink  but we need to change the code that creates a new course version from an old course version  so that it disregards course local files. ### Comments One could argue that both the above scenarios are valid. Depending on how one use LenaSYS. Perhaps we should implement both and give the user a choice when creating the new course version? Either way  giving a brief description of what is done during the copy process should be given so that a new user knows what has been done I think is a good thing. A third scenario based on timestamps could perhaps be used. This will also require a path column. I am unsure if this is usable solution though. I have a feeling that this would break our global -** course -** course version idea though.');
