INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4172,'4172','2018-03-21T20:30:34Z',1540,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Very confusing use of pen AND cog wheel in Course Editor','Remove new course version pen icon as this is covered more or less completely by functionality available in the version dropdown in sectioned. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880137735631-ef8607fe-2d4e-11e8-9b65-89a41197b910.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4173,'4173','2018-03-21T20:47:54Z',1540,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Fileed has database search for files','Remove Database Search in Fileed and change it to a sortable table version. A normal looking-glass dialog Perhaps integrating the looking glass icon with the text box  like how the version dropdown to the top left corner of the section editor. Instead of searching in the database we can search interactively using the functionality from sortabletable. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880137736477-521da992-2d51-11e8-82b6-84eb60265ae2.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4174,'4174','2018-03-21T21:06:49Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Live markdown preview in file editor','For example by a pen icon or a button for .md files could allow direct editing of markdown files. A view much like the marking preview window. Data file to the left and markdown preview to the right. A save button that saves the edited mardown text to the corresponding file. This editing should only work for .md files.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4175,'4175','2018-03-21T21:20:28Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Mini mode  blue mushroom mode ','For the marking a mini-mode has been requested. A second rendering mode accessible by a button or check box somewhere...  in filter dialog?  By checking this box we render the whole marking view with a reduced size to allow us to get a reduced size preview of the whole course  e.g. if we have 30 tests and 80 students in a course . Using sortable table we just change the rendering callback to render this specific mode if a box is ticked Render all marking buttons inoperative  this is a viewing mode only. Render students names in a reduced single line mode with only the name of the student and no ssn etc Only show color of cells  green for G or VG  yellow for un-marked and red for failed tests. It should not be possible to click anything or selectmark anything. Sorting of columns should happen normally.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4176,'4176','2018-03-21T21:23:47Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Sum at bottom of columns','Since sums are a free feature of using sortable table library we can sum the number of yellow assignments  at the bottom of each column.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4177,'4177','2018-03-21T21:25:50Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Open','Filter on examiner in marking view','We need an interactive looking glass filter in the marking view Implemented for free by using sortable table If we write the name of an examiner in this box only students examined by this teacher are shown. This filter is remembered if one returns to that page later on.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4178,'4178','2018-03-21T21:29:16Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Filter in marking view for teachers responsible for marking this specific test','Similarly to #4177 we need a filter for marking teacher. Each test  dugga  should have a marking teacher for it. A teacher is selected from a drop-down containing all teachers in the course. Each test has one or more teachers as a comma-separated list The looking glass should allow us to search for only assignments shortlisted for any specific teacher written in looking-glass text box.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4179,'4179','2018-03-21T21:35:05Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Control+Click to change incorrect mark','In the marking view we want the ability to fix erroneous clicks e.g. if one accidentally fails the wrong student by clicking the wrong line. Control+click on other mark changes the mark to this mark Only allowed within a short time-span - after let us say 10 minutes the control+click method is not possible for reverting mark It should be possible to revert from any mark to any other mark or not-yet-marked');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4180,'4180','2018-03-21T21:45:08Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Mobile formatting of section editor is not quite there yet...','The layout still breaks Text is drawn on top of other text Deadline date is reduced in size when screen is small  e.g. year is removed We need ellipses on the heading text when text does not fit eg. PHP ... Text label should not wrap to two lines under any circumstances There is also an exclamation point triangle shown if we submit after the deadline. This occupies far too much space it should only occupy a few pixels  24px in width an height  also  the icon is a png not an svg. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880137738967-fb3aff50-2d58-11e8-91c9-3110fa2cbed0.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4181,'4181','2018-03-21T21:54:32Z',1540,22,'HGustavs','Closed','Retaining collapsed-state of sections in local storage','For each course viewed in the browser the collapse-states of each element should be remembered. If all parts of the course execpt for the first is collapsed and we return to the course this should still be the case - currently we are returned to the full-all-elements-expanded view. Standardized way to remember these settings. Preferably a library that we can make part of the code base which helps with this task. This code can then be shared between groups as this is needed in more than one part of the code.');
