INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4198,'4198','2018-03-22T09:41:52Z',1541,10,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram editing settings dialogs','Currently the way that settings dialogs work is a bit of a problem from a code standard and programming standpoint As can be seen in the screnshot of the folder structure below... the settings-dialogs are individual static dialogs that are populated when a diagram object is created. In order to follow the code standard we need to have a single service file that does all back-end stuff i.e. diagram_service.php We need one file that has all the static html dialogs content i.e. diagram.php We need one file that handles all these dialogs  also no need to have distinct dialogs for distinct content  one dialog that is changed to fit each kind of diagram entity.  as can be seen below  entity and relation are exactly identical  I suggest splitting this into a few smaller sub-issues. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880137762718-7151bd82-2dbd-11e8-9ca3-9ecdfebc0591.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4199,'4199','2018-03-22T09:43:49Z',1541,10,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram editing changes mode all the time','I select draw entity. An entiy is drawn Wen I move to draw my second entity  instead of drawing entity I have reverted to select mode. Normally one draws a set of diagram objects at the same time  imaginde drawing five attributes  and having to push draw entity each time ');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4200,'4200','2018-03-22T10:23:41Z',1541,11,'HGustavs','Closed','When making diagram object settings is automatically shown','When we draw a diagram object  the settings dialog is shown always. This is not helpful for a fast working process  if I draw an entity  and then want to draw five attributes: I want to be able to click entity  draw the entity  Click attribute and click five times to get the five attributes. Move attributes or entities them so they are placed evenly on screen. Then I write the names of each attribute. Currently the work process is Click entity Click ok in settings dialog Click attribute Click ok in settings dialog Click attribute  sigh!  Click ok in settings dialog  again! sigh!  Imagine drawing five entities with five attributes each.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4201,'4201','2018-03-22T10:33:42Z',1541,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Proper selection marker in Diagram Editor','Currently the selection marker is a near invisible change in the one pixel border of the graphical element.... In addition to making the border considerably thicker  how about also adding powerpoint style selection markers. I think there may already be code for drawing small x-pixel large boxes that can be used for this  or such a small utility function can be created in diagram.js [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880137765588-d182cf82-2dc4-11e8-8c69-0840525f3d11.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(4202,'4202','2018-03-22T10:36:35Z',1541,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Questionable defaults','When one draws a new entity it has black text on black background? Or is it random color? I suggest using the pervasive white fill and relatively thick black line as the no-action-default.');
