INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6303,'6304','2019-04-25T20:23:14Z',1940,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Contribution hourly chart','I would like an hourly chart in addition to the weekly chart currently available Something like this On hours above some treshold e.g. 5%  we paint a hoverable rectangle with detailed info. It would be nice to show commit activity  issue activity etc in different colors ... Displaying what hours a person has been committingissue-writing and so on. A decidedly nebulous view  depictinig only the hours of each type and computing the percentage compared to total... but nevertheless and estimate at which hours a person is most active. Eg. If commits are green... and the user has made one commit on 21th of march at 13:12 and one commit at 15:35. The 13 point would show 50% and the 15 point would show 50% and we would see 13:00-14:00 50% activity 1 commit total of 2. in the hover view. At the same time we could see a polygon for events  showing the corresponding information for events  but in another color for example yellow might look like above. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880156765495-79130600-67a7-11e9-8ca3-845e09baa026.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6731,'6732','2019-05-08T08:58:23Z',1953,9,'a97marbr','Closed','Unnessecary max-width?','It seems that we have a max-width on our table columns when grading  but if there is room why not use the space? [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com494866157362845-f5caba80-717f-11e9-8c8f-562bdabd38c6.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6915,'6916','2019-05-12T08:49:50Z',1957,9,'HGustavs','Open','Feedback Test Test Feedback Head Scratcher','This is an on-goinglong-running hard-to-pinpoint issue in the feedback system. The problem stems from an earlier bug in the handling of tests. When a person clicks on a test  a variant of that test is assigned to the person. Fair enough. There is also a moment item corresponding to the test - and for some reason  an instance of that data is created for each moment The feedback given for the test is connected to that test for that test item. There are circumstances when strange things happen. When we give more than one item of feedback When we assign a mark but immediately revoke that mark  control click or click again  and enter another mark and new feedback Especially in the feedback-test but same error has ocurred in the normal exams also  but has perhaps been fixed by now? This then happens: While entering feedback the teacher sees a complete history of old feedback items When students view their feedback they see nothing When teacher leaves the feedback view and re-enters it  no feedback is shown or a random item of feedback is shown So.... I would like the following: Documentation of the database changes with test data entered into the issue so we can document and triage the problem Detailed diagnosis Suggestions for a fix');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6916,'6917','2019-05-12T08:55:19Z',1957,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Marking with incorrect feedback','This is the scenario One views a document  using the marking preview window  and writes some feedback  and sets a mark in that view. One sets a mark by clicking directly in the marking view ... without previewing anything first. The logical thing would be for the first mark be given with the feedback... which predictably is what happens. However  the second mark  which is thought to be given without feedback  has the same feedback as the previous item. Not good  especially if we are marking different students. I am thinking this is a relatively simple issue of not clearing the feedback dialog after setting a mark for a student? Unclear if this happes for ordinary exams and for feedback exams only.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6917,'6918','2019-05-12T09:06:21Z',1957,10,'HGustavs','Open','Additional icon for previewing student submissions?','Right now AFAIK we have two icons for viewing student hand-in? One icon for viewing using the built in feedback tool allowing preview and marking in same view. One icon for downloadingviewing the file.  correct me if wrong so far....  Other options are possible Download only pdf  https:stackoverflow.comquestions6794255html-download-a-pdf-file-instead-of-opening-them-in-browser-when-clicked  Download and preview  pdf in same tab  Download and preview  pdf in new tab  I am thinking ... Pop-out can be achieved by right-click open in new tab.... but I wouldnt be completely against an icon for that also.... along with an icon for forced download. What does it do right now and how can we make the interface for this even better?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6918,'6919','2019-05-12T09:55:41Z',1957,10,'HGustavs','Open','Feedback set phrases per course','Currently feedback is only a text box We have a add button which is though to work as a set phrases box. however. We want to be able to add set phrases for the course directly from the text. So if i select a range of text that I want to add to the set phrases box  i click add to box button and it magically appears in the box as a set phrase for this course. That interface allows us to add from the text box to the drop-down. ...but... I would really be able to add longer stretches of text..... such as I really appreciate the layout of the report  but I find the background lacking in detail If we do that... the dropdown is no longer suitable as a medium. How about a tag cloud with the most common set phrases  10? 8?  for this feedback item plus a dropdown for more rarely used ones. The dropdown list should be for the set phrases from the course but the common response list should be for the specific feedback item.... The dropdowntag should only show the firs few words of the phrase and an ellipses. A bit like the suggest box in github but with a dropdown and not a text box.. and two columns of phrases rather than the single item per row layout of github.  e.g. 5-6 rows of two tags per row   When a set phrase is used more often in the course feedback item it moves up the list from the dropdown to the bottom of the tag list... or even to the top of it if commonly used. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com697880157580526-08f4c780-74ab-11e9-9d63-fc68109193d2.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(6941,'6942','2019-05-13T09:46:11Z',1958,10,'HGustavs','Open','Web browser push notifications of new results','Push notifications of results to web browsers. We would like a service worker interface for sending notifications to the web browser. There used to be a push notification service but  it was too complicated to maintain. A minimum interface that users can subscribe to get results only. When a result is added to a student we want this to be sent as a notification to students that have elected for notifications of results. We only want to send new result available in course XXX... Not complete data including marks and so on. As far as I understand it  this has to be implemented by polling for each student? In that case I suggest polling every 10 minutes  configurable  to reduce server load. https:developer.mozilla.orgen-USdocsWebAPIPush_API');
