INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9781,'9782','2021-02-24T19:31:47Z',2611,20,'HGustavs','Open','File lists for uploaded zip-files','If we upload a zip-file  the short-linked preview should show the name of the file and the link but also a directory listing of the zip file. This way a teacher can see if for example the correct type of files have been uploaded without having to decompress zip file.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9782,'9783','2021-02-24T19:51:19Z',2611,20,'HGustavs','Closed','Remove assignment pane from course contents','As we are moving towards closer integration with canvas we need to support iframe linking of the course pages. The assignment pane is thus not needed and can be removed from the course view. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801109057436-03995900-76e2-11eb-8bfc-c8177659b081.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9783,'9784','2021-03-23T08:33:05Z',2638,9,'HGustavs','Closed','Local storage item for current assignment variant','In order to getting the same variant when re-visiting the dugga we need to keep track of the previously used variant when re-visiting the assignment page.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9784,'9785','2021-03-27T10:00:41Z',2642,11,'HGustavs','Open','Template literals where applicable','In all non-deprecated places we should replace the current string based system with template literals. For example __body** can remain as is... But __body**__div**+str+__div**__body** should be replaced with __body**__div**$str__div**__body** or even __body** __div**$str__div** __body** If the line is very long  in this case the string is too short to split into multiple lines ');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9785,'9786','2021-03-28T15:17:48Z',2643,16,'HGustavs','Open','Diagram json synchronization','Previous years have had problems with the size of the json data. Even a very small diagram  only a few entities  would very soon reach a large size  megabytes  when stored as json. I have added a few default objects... I suggest an algorithm: Comparing to the default objects and only store the values that are not the same as the defaults Only storing the properties that are present in the demo dataset  since we add for example x1 y1 x2 y2 computed from left top and widthheight ... we only want to store the significant properties that are not computed from other properties.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9786,'9787','2021-03-28T15:28:49Z',2643,16,'HGustavs','Closed','Robust change detection in diagram editor','Since the data for a diagram contains the full data for  most  previous versions of the diagram  we can decide how often to make a new version of the diagram. This has been discussed in several previous issues. [ version 1 diagram data  version 2 diagram data  version 3 diagram data ] We want to store the current diagram at the last item in the dataset  in this case version 3   which is the diagram shown on screen. After a number of changes e.g. making an attribute  change name of attribute  move attribute we can decide to make a new version  so that any future updates then happen in version 4 diagram data which at first is a copy of version 3 diagram data ...');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9787,'9788','2021-03-28T15:32:51Z',2643,16,'HGustavs','Closed','Replacing the diagram module with new diagram core','A new diagram core has been created in https:github.comHGustavsDiagramEngine This new svg and html based engine should completely replace the canvas-based engine in the previous diagram module');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9788,'9789','2021-03-28T15:33:59Z',2643,16,'HGustavs','Open','Creating diagram-dugga','A dugga needs to be created for submitting diagram duggas.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9789,'9790','2021-03-28T15:54:39Z',2643,16,'HGustavs','Open','Individual assignment log-in  so students do not need to log in ','I am not sure to what extent this issue is covered by previous issues  We need a new single assignment-log-in system for assignments. When we press save  currently we receive a dialog with a code. The new version needs to Change that dialog into a single assignment hand-in login. We need: An url to the assignment data A uniquely generated password for that assignment hand-in This way the student can submit the url to an assignment  but return back to the same assignment by using the password  it is thus possible to complete a previous assignment by adding more files or continue working on an interactive assignment.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9790,'9791','2021-03-28T19:05:44Z',2643,20,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram line overlay layer is above entities not below','We need to use css to move the overlay layer containing svg lines to a level below the entities. Currently the lines are drawn on top of the entities.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9791,'9792','2021-03-28T20:28:29Z',2643,21,'HGustavs','Closed','Center Left alignment of text in diagram','If text is longer than the space inside the symbol we currently have clipping of the text The issue with this is that we clip both the beginning and the end of the text. Procurement would read curem with the rest of the text clipped away. We should use centering if the text is short so that Owns is centerd in the middle of the attribute or relationship symbol for example. But if the left edge of the text is to the left of the left edge of the symbol the text should remain to the left. something like place left edge of text half of the width of the text to the left of the center of the symbol  but if that resulting value is less than the left of the symbol we should assign the position of the left of the text to the left edge of the symbol. The result is centering until the beginning of the text is occluded  and after that we align the left edge of the text to the left edge of the symbol. The key line drawing function has a function for the estimation of text length.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9792,'9793','2021-03-29T08:52:26Z',2644,9,'HGustavs','Open','Update code standard','Code standard needs to be updated with project-wide rules for using template literals.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9793,'9794','2021-03-29T10:01:12Z',2644,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Making Access editor Teacher Only','The access editor should remove columns for personal numbers an so on and only contain information relevant for teachers');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9794,'9795','2021-03-29T13:28:23Z',2644,14,'HGustavs','Closed','No downloads when viewing submissions  file submission dugga ','Teachers should still see the normal view but .. students should only see the file names andor file list from zip files. Other types of duggas are not affected by this change  and should function as always');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9795,'9796','2021-03-29T13:35:29Z',2644,14,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram lines extend to nearly the edge of the box','We have a safety margin around each box so that we have ample space to draw the lines in the svg Relationship lines are however drawn only to the edge of the box and not to the edge of the diagram symbol wihch is a few units further down the line. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801112844738-5c269200-90a4-11eb-8d70-1894e4f95ed1.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9796,'9797','2021-03-29T13:43:14Z',2644,14,'HGustavs','Closed','Remove color from bulbs in section editor','Until more complete integration with canvas has been achieved we need to remove the bulb colors from the section editor. All bulbs should remain gray even if a student has submitted an assignment since there is no way for lenasys to know if the user has submitted an assignment or not. Also remove any related parts of the css in order to simplify the css file.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9797,'9798','2021-03-29T14:23:04Z',2644,15,'HGustavs','Open','Redirection functionality','We need a robust way to redirect  LenaSYSDuggaSyssh  from: short url to student assignment e.g. dugga.his.sesh2fc6e1 will redirect to saved assignment submission course name to most recent version of course content ... currently the link looks like this https:dugga.iit.his.seDuggaSyssectioned.php?courseid=4&coursename=Databaskonstruktion&coursevers=82452 ... the URL shortener should redirect us to that link from shDatabaskonstruktion ... when we change from 2021 version of to 2022 version we will arrive at the correct location ... this is so that the link in canvas will not need to be updated assignment redirection to specific assignment in course e.g. shDatabaskonstruktion?ass=MVC in order to arrive to https:dugga.iit.his.seDuggaSysshowDugga.php?did=1326&cid=4&coursevers=82452&moment=9241&segment=9218&highscoremode=0&comment=null&deadline=2020-12-16%2017:00:00 or https:dugga.iit.his.seDuggaSysshowDugga.php?did=1326&cid=4&coursevers=82452&moment=9241 with some of the un-needed stuff stripped from the URL. The current code is merely a stub showing functionality. We need to connect this to the database so that the correct assignment course is shown.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9798,'9799','2021-03-29T15:09:39Z',2644,16,'HGustavs','Closed','Removing menu bar for linked page','Currently this is what lenasys looks like when embedded into canvas [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801112857819-8894db00-90b1-11eb-94a9-e8ce67c6fcb8.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9799,'9800','2021-03-29T15:20:46Z',2644,16,'HGustavs','Open','Accessibility adaptation of lenasys','We are currently required by law to have good accesibility on our sites. Lenasys does not quite live up to these requirements. I suggest checking lenasys with some accessibility tool such as lighthouse https:developers.google.comwebtoolslighthouse ...and then add issues for any accessibility problems encountered. Begin with the easiest to solve  and progress from there  creating new sub-issues when needed.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9800,'9801','2021-03-30T08:17:50Z',2645,9,'a97marbr','Closed','Demo Issue 2021','This is a demo issue');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9801,'9802','2021-03-30T10:01:50Z',2645,11,'a97marbr','Closed','Update install.php','Made requested edit.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9830,'9831','2021-04-03T22:35:35Z',2649,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Code standard in diagram editor','I am not sure that I like the formatting of this line  and a few similar ones close to it  if  ! x2__=x&&x__=x1   return false; I think I prefer if  ! x2__=x&&x__=x1   return false; Which is clearer to me.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9831,'9832','2021-04-03T22:45:01Z',2649,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Section editor side bar moving swimlanes to top and bug fix swim lanes','When integrating with canvas we lack screen width for the sidebar... also we do not know to what extent assignments have been handed in. However the swimlane display at the bottom of the sidebar is still relevant  as it does not show personal information  but rather the current week and assignment deadlines within course. I would like to see a proposal for a re-designed swimlade display that is suitable for the top of the screen  rather than as a side bar. I would prefer that we use the full width of the area rather than the limited width of the side bar. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801113493291-5b479300-94de-11eb-958b-f27d997743f3.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9832,'9833','2021-04-03T22:48:38Z',2649,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Section editor swimlane modernization','...I do believe that the swim lanes functionality does not work for courses that are longer than 10 weeks  for example the final year project ..... Also if the deadline has not yet been updated for the current year it would be nice if we could still have a guesstimate for the deadlines transposed to the current year in the swimlane display  and some kind of display using coloring or other graphics indicating that the deadline has not been updated for the current year yet... [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801113493376-0a846a00-94df-11eb-915d-c7e1e3853f81.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9833,'9834','2021-04-03T23:33:54Z',2650,0,'HGustavs','Closed','Removing access category and group assignment from access editor','As students will not appear in the database  only teachers  this means that we can remove the access and group columns from the access editor. Furthermore  in this issue and also in a file in the repository  document which columns and which tables that need to be removed from the database to implement this change. Due to the no refactoring rule  we can probably not physically remove these columns without disrupting functionality in the sort term  but we can document this in a clear and concise manner for future use.');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9834,'9835','2021-04-05T13:57:39Z',2651,14,'HGustavs','Closed','Rulers in diagram editor','I would really like some photoshop-style rulers in the diagram editor Including a colored line representing the position of the pointer [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801113581606-a15c3e00-9627-11eb-8e3d-66e476820f2d.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9835,'9836','2021-04-05T14:12:30Z',2651,15,'HGustavs','Open','Contribution tool commit lines of code files affected','The current version of the contribution tool does not show the size of commits I would like to visualize the size of the commits in some manner  for example the size of the circle could be larger if more lines are committed. A second related issue is that there is no legend showing what each of the lines represent [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801113583151-90143100-9629-11eb-877b-80540cdf8397.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9836,'9837','2021-04-05T14:15:08Z',2651,15,'HGustavs','Open','Contribution tool clock','I feel that the clock functionality is not very controllable. The display is very nice in general. Unclear what the colors mean  and I would really like to see commits issues etc as separate areas under the graph Unclear what the gradient inside the reactangle denotes if anything? Also it seems that we can not give course weeks and that there strangely enough is only one date setting. I would prefer to choose course weeks that both start and end the interval  1-6 or 1-10 or 5-10 for example .');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9845,'9846','2021-04-06T11:49:45Z',2652,12,'HGustavs','Open','Diagram text measuring functionality','If no other smarter text measuring functionality  making a canvas and using text measuring from html5 canvas  which is used in previous diagram version  is considered too cumbersome  is found  I suggest making similar relative measuring functionality for the capital letters also... and as a stretch goal  also supporting some other font as a parameter to the measuring function. HGustavsDiagramEngine@a5022cf');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9869,'9870','2021-04-07T10:27:11Z',2653,11,'HGustavs','Closed','Section editor refactoring bug from project course 2020','The project course in 2020 broke the no refactoring rule in an incompatible manner. Version 0.12  before project 2020 version  works well evidenced by screenshot below With the same data the startup project 2021 version does not work It seems like a new incompatible column tabs was added to the database to store the existing tabs data in a new place. This makes the application completely incompatible with existing installations  which is the whole purpose of LenaSYS  ... Previously the tab count was stored in the gradesys column  since an element can not be both tabbed and have a grade at the same time . We must revert this change so that the tabs are once again read and stored in the gradesys column. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801113851638-ff119700-979b-11eb-98c4-3d4e0a2f45dd.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9944,'9945','2021-04-09T19:35:58Z',2655,20,'HGustavs','Closed','Pressing escape should cancel most mouse modes in diagrams','If the user is mid drag-scroll or mid-move or mid-entity-line  or most other mouse modes  and the user changes hisher mid  as one does  pushing the escape key should act as a general canceling of that mouse mode without changing the objectsscroll positionetc');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9945,'9946','2021-04-09T22:05:08Z',2655,23,'HGustavs','Closed','Attribute properties','The distinct states of er attributes are mutually exclusive  an attribute can not be both a multiple value and a key at the same time for instance. I think we can use a dropdown instead of three individual boooleans  this way we can guarantee that we dont have multiple computed attributes or some other unsupported combination. We can use the defaults to store the list of options. The first of which we can use as the default value. HGustavsDiagramEngine@b8e8f8c Dropdowns for controlling properties can perhaps be used in other locations for other mutually exclusive properties?');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9984,'9985','2021-04-12T15:39:29Z',2658,16,'HGustavs','Open','The diagram dugga has a purple top toolbar','If embedded as an iframe or if a full screen icon is clicked the purple top menu should disappear and the side bar should be top to bottom [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801114422527-a7699600-9bb6-11eb-8cba-92a043131aac.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(9985,'9986','2021-04-12T15:52:47Z',2658,16,'HGustavs','Closed','Diagram cursor modes as tool bar','I think there is a previous issue for creating an illustrator photoshop -style drawing-tool-bar in addition to the side-bar for drawing on the diagram. Currently we have buttons in the property side-bar. Perhaps we can move the zooming functionality there too... more commonly used features in the draw menu and object properties or more rarely used functionality in the sidebar. Also horizontal vertical view of toolbar using flexbox would be a good idea. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801114422836-ea2b6e00-9bb6-11eb-9158-bdc92ecdd84b.png]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(10091,'10092','2021-04-15T14:40:42Z',2661,15,'HGustavs','Open','Diagram does not avoid crossing lines automatically','Seeded version of diagram engine  from https:github.comHGustavsDiagramEngine  avoids crossing lines  but the current LenaSYS code does not. [https:user-images.githubusercontent.com6978801114888086-3b32a080-9e09-11eb-8441-dab8d43fd649.gif]');
INSERT INTO issue VALUES(10242,'10243','2021-04-20T17:41:05Z',2666,18,'HGustavs','Open','Code standard not followed by diagram','The diagram code is not consistent when following the code standard. The code standard for LenaSYS is K&R  and much of the code does not follow this style. https:en.wikipedia.orgwikiIndentation_style#K&R_style A few examples for  var i = 0; i __ data.length; i++  __--- should be up here __--- A curly brace here indicates a function and not a for-loop __--- else should be at most one space character from this curly brace  no new line else if event.target.classList.contains node   __---- else should be here else if  mouseMode == mouseModes.POINTER  __--- curly brace should be here ');
