INSERT INTO event VALUES(8250,'1218','2015-05-04T10:11:15Z',488,11,'HGustavs','comment','Well  my view is that the data in init_db has to be global  and working for all..... otherwise  one group may have working code that breaks things for some other group. If both groups have the same data and the master database is reset to the contents of init_db each week  there will be no database related errors due to divergent information content. The larger issue is how to decide what to put in the database.... well as always  work incrementally  rarely if ever removing something. Agree with other groups what information to put in the file.... and if all groups try to work incrementally  there should be a joint test dataset within a week. The main goal is that all groups work with the same dataset.... and that every person works with the same dataset  with local additions for testing work features  and when those features are stable  merge that data into the joint dataset. The end goal is that the databases between team members and between the different subgroups differ as little as possible.','UNK');
