INSERT INTO event VALUES(13943,'1926','2016-04-06T17:08:12Z',826,18,'HGustavs','comment','To clarify my position: I want the following: A tested and working script for clearing the database in case one breaks it A script for inserting test data that is taken from real courses with real information needs. If we want to test a dugga variant for a test student we can do this using that insert after clearing the database if we want to test if it works on a fresh install. This also makes sense for student developers as they have a single agreed-upon set of test data to run the system through. I am not very invested in if this is done in 1-2 or 3 files. but that functionality is what I want from a development standpoint. and... that SQL code should be human-readable and properly commented. At some point someone recreated the sql by exporting from a the database using a sql tool such as mysql workbench.... which made the code much less standardized and less readable than before.','UNK');
