INSERT INTO event VALUES(17405,'2297','2016-05-02T09:51:30Z',852,10,'HGustavs','comment','Many questions. We can try to put the discussion in this issue? Im thinking replace is a strong word  allowing as an option would perhaps be a less divisive way to say it? Options for a graduated approach  on a per-course basis  andor for editing only. In-line editing of code in lenasys  is a long-term stretch goal of this project. Are there benefits that outweigh the risks for a view-only scenario? What candidates are there? Are there features in ace that are indispensible?  is there a better code viewereditor than ace ? If there is an issue with the editor  we expose only teachers to it and only when live-editing code would be less risky than exposing all students all the time. An inline-editor only approach with a pop-over would probably be the easiest to implement? What does a full editor give us that a more passive viewer does not? Viewer only is preferred over editor with disabled functionality.','UNK');
