INSERT INTO event VALUES(19041,'2467','2017-03-22T22:32:21Z',1176,23,'HGustavs','comment','I strongly prefer not splitting the symbol or giagram classes further e.g. a er-entity class or a er-attribute class.... I want this functionality encapsulated within a single class in order to make the code as small and generic as possible.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(19043,'2467','2017-03-29T12:35:30Z',1183,13,'HGustavs','comment','I would say no on the name change as the rest of the project has standardized naming of user interface stuff. e.g. sectioned.php __- Static user interface sectioned.js __- User interface code sectionedservice.php __- Data service Im thinking we try to adhere to this rule as much as possible  and only make incremental update by adding specialized files in addition to the standard ones.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(19045,'2467','2017-03-29T13:51:04Z',1183,14,'HGustavs','comment','Figures are a collections of lines and fills etc that can be used to create a software such as illustrator or to draw custom shapes in a diagram. Symbols are glyphs in a diagram e.g. ER entity  UML Class etc that have properties like names and so on. So if we want to draw for instance a border line around parts of the diagram to indicate which group is the owner of that part of the diagram  we do that with a figure.... but each of the diagram symbols such as entitites or classes are drawn using symbols.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(19046,'2467','2017-03-29T13:58:46Z',1183,14,'HGustavs','comment','The pink part is a figure and the rest of the diagram is composed of symbols. I suggest we start out with the symbols  one diagram at a time and then move on to figures if there is time.','UNK');
