INSERT INTO event VALUES(57882,'6330','2019-04-26T10:37:16Z',1941,11,'HGustavs','comment','This is not a bug. In the database the data stored should use ampersand o u m l semicolon but it seems the some displaying converts this to something else in some place? Perhaps the code converts the ampersand character to ampersand a m p semicolon If the html code is unchanged from database to screen we get swedish characters on screen. Im thiniking that if this is not displayed correctly  the solution is to convert to proper ampersand character and the text should automatically show swedish character. By storing the data in html coded format we do not have to be reliant on a utf-8 path from screen to database... but the cost is that we do need to make sure that it is handled consistently in this manner. Changing database types etc is a huge refactoring issue  so even if we could solve it by making changes in the database other things would decidedly break. Php and apache are notoriously finicky when it comes to utf-8','UNK');
