INSERT INTO event VALUES(80880,'7902','2020-04-09T07:19:55Z',2290,8,'HGustavs','comment','This is a KEY feature of this system If someone draws a diagram. Teachers want to be able to play the history of that diagram from beginning to end with something akin to a play button to see how the diagram was drawn over time. So we want the history for this and for undoing changes and seamlessly being able to move back to a previous state not just by ctrl-z but like a play interface in an instruction video on youtube. However','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(80881,'7902','2020-04-09T07:23:38Z',2290,8,'HGustavs','comment','This should not make use of several megabytes. If we add an entity. How much should that take up? Lets say for arguments sake 200 bytes. Then we can have 5000 entities or 5000 state changes on one entity per megabyte. Also we do not want to store every single miniscule update of the diagram... If an entity is moved around a lot  and we place it in 10 different positions before adding the next entity. Perhaps some of those places can be ignored. Perhaps we only store changes every x seconds or only when new items are added. Also the information is VERY un-compact. We store truefalse when we could store 1 or 0 ... making the data 5 times larger for no benefit compared to the space it occupies. We can call symbolkind sk reducing the number of bytes of that property by a fifth. We also had discussions last year about omitting empty data from the textual version. Since neither operations:[] or attributes:[] contain anything I would ommit that data completely  reducing that information from nearly 30 bytes to 0 for storing that  lack of  information.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(80882,'7902','2020-04-09T07:35:41Z',2290,8,'HGustavs','comment','There are LOTS of issues that can be handed out for compressing this information by reducing the data without loss of information.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(80883,'7902','2020-04-09T07:36:39Z',2290,8,'HGustavs','comment','Also we want ONE diagram at at time. When we swap diagram it should be synched from file only one instance in local storage at a time.','UNK');
