INSERT INTO event VALUES(108219,'9778','2021-04-06T15:25:27Z',2652,16,'HGustavs','comment','Each time a person presses save a new random number is created. This number is hashed so the number can not easily be deduced from the hash string. This hash and a random password for this specific assignment hand-in can then be used to return to this exact assignment using the redirection feature. It is this url to this hash that the student hands in to canvas. There is thus no way to deduce which student made which hand-in outside of canvas.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(108220,'9778','2021-04-06T15:31:24Z',2652,16,'HGustavs','comment','The process is as follows: The student thus goes to an assignment  finishes the assignment  when the student presses save the random hash  for example FCE45F37  is generated together with a password the student can use to return to that specific hand-in The student then makes note of the password and hash for that assignment hand-in. The student then paste-s for example FCE45F37 into the assignment which the teacher can then asess and mark inside of the canvas installation. This way the students do not log in to lenasys  and no personal information that can be traced back to the studnet is stored in lenasys. But the teacher can then review the assignment in the normal fashion inside of the canvas installation','UNK');
