INSERT INTO event VALUES(108854,'9870','2021-04-07T20:46:11Z',2653,21,'HGustavs','comment','It is a problem with the rendering of course entries i.e. the section editor The problem is that for the year 2020 in the project course it seems like the developers added a column for tabs  which previously was stored in gradesys. This is refactoring and is incompatible with existing courses since existing courses store the tab number in the gradesys column. Since older versions of the data does not have the column the easiest way to test for the bug is removing that column  as it is in the existing installations . So what we need is to revert back that change  and storing the tab count in the gradesys column again. We must make sure that we do not allow storing of a tab count when we actually need the gradesys  moment i.e. delkurs  as this would over-write the gradesys value.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(108855,'9870','2021-04-07T20:49:06Z',2653,21,'HGustavs','comment','The most common way to solve added columns is to add an empty column with that name for existing data. If we just add an empty column tabs to existing courses  we effectively remove all tabs in all existing courses  and all previous iterations of a course  which for obvious reasons is unacceptable. So we are required to mitigate the effects of that refactoring.','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(108857,'9870','2021-04-12T15:19:12Z',2658,16,'HGustavs','comment','if you run the code ALTER TABLE listentries DROP COLUMN tabs; you are at the same state as any running server  which do not have that column  so I would start there. Without this column no errors should happen. Have you removed this column and no errors occur? In that case sql errors have been disabled on the server since  the code in the service tries to store values or retrieve values from a column that does not exist  since we just removed that column with the alter table above  non-existing columns must result in errors in any sql dialect .','UNK');
INSERT INTO event VALUES(108858,'9870','2021-04-12T15:25:09Z',2658,16,'HGustavs','comment','So: Step 1 Remove tab column  we can never change behavior of existing column due to refactoring rule  Step 2 Make sure tabs are read from gradesys column Step 3 Store tab count in gradesys column on update Step 4 fix inserts so no tabs column is used Step 3b Make sure we do not store tabs in gradesys coulmn for moment object since they use gradesys to store the grade system for that moment.','UNK');
