INSERT INTO event VALUES(109291,'9915','2021-04-09T19:51:07Z',2655,20,'HGustavs','comment','Im thinking of this like creating checkpoints  and we try to minimize the number of checkpoints and the amounmakwt of information stored in those checkpoints. If we move the same object several times  we synchronize with the top version  but if we add another entity we create a new version. And each time we compare with the defaults and only store the properties of each object in the history that differ from the defaults and from the previous version in the history. When we read from the history we start with the default and only add update properties that have been changed. I am hoping that we thus should be possible to push a play button and view the diagram as a movie from the empty sheet to the finished diagram. if we move back in the history and make changes from that point  everything past that moment should be discarded. We do not plan to keep branched histories like git does.','UNK');
